      },
      "date": "2018-10-16 16:04:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nGreat question and I don't have a good answer. With ha.sh as it is now, there is no way to send in command line variables. See my comment for a future solution. \n\nSince we can't run ha in our autotest, I would remove the \"testlist=ha\" and we will just have to inspect the code with no results. If you have results/output, you could post it here or in the ticket.\n\nThanks for expanding this script.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
